            <title>[SOLR-5834] Overseer threads are only being interrupted and not closed.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5834</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As noticed by Hossman in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5823&quot; title=&quot;Add utility function for internal code to know if it is currently the overseer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5823&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5823&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the Overseer is not actually calling close on the runnables that are used to create threads - the treads are only being interrupted in Overseer#close, but not closed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
